On 15 March 2012, the Board of Directors of Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (the "Company") amended the Company's Amended and Restated Bylaws to eliminate the exclusive forum provision in Article VIII, Section 7. This provision mandated that the Court of Chancery for the State of Delaware be the exclusive forum for derivative claims brought on behalf of the Company, breach of fiduciary duty claims involving the officers, directors, or employees of the Company, and any other action involving the Company asserting a claim arising under the Delaware General Corporation law or governed by the internal affairs doctrine.
